n','n','','','','','','','','','','','',0,0,0,'','n',0,'','',0,'n'),(38,'2008-06-19 16:15:30','CIM Group','Investments','6922 Hollywood Boulevard','Suite 900','Los Angeles','CA','90028','US','www.cimgroup.com','Medium (50 - 500 employees)','CIM Group, Inc. is an integrated, full service real estate private equity firm that invests on behalf of its principals, partners and investors.  Since 1993, CIM has successfully employed an urban investment strategy with in-house research, development, finance, leasing and property management capabilities to acquire and develop over 13 million square feet of urban properties at a total cost of over $4.5 billion.  CIM embraces the urbanization movement currently underway throughout the United States, focusing on urban and infill communities within traditional downtown areas, transit corridors, and suburban main streets positioned for transformation through significant public and private investment and development. CIM invests in top tier metropolitan markets in all property types (mixed-use, retail, apartment, condominium, office, entertainment, parking, signage and infill land development) through direct acquisitions, joint venture investments and public-private partnerships.  CIM approaches urban investment from a “community-based” perspective and applies creative solutions and the understanding, patience and determination to make successful investments for CIM, our partners and the local community.  \r\n\r\nCIM is headquartered in Los Angeles, CA with investment offices in Bethesda, MD and San Francisco, CA.  CIM is currently managing three multi-billion investment funds on behalf of institutional investors:  CIM Fund, CIM Fund III and the CIM Urban REIT, which combined allow CIM to invest across the full spectrum of real estate assets from stabilized properties to ground-up development.','n','n','n','y','y','y','y','y','y','y','','','','',0,0,0,'','n',0,'','',0,'n'),(39,'2008-06-19 17:34:02','Lockheed Martin','','6801 Rockledge Drive','','Bethesda','MD','20817','US','','Large (>500 employees)','Lockheed Martin is a highly diversified $39.6 billion advanced technology company and the strategic leader in the aerospace industry with major positions in information systems, software development, space, launch vehicles, aeronautics, electronics, environmental services, and energy programs.  The vision of the Corporation is to be the world’s premier systems engineering and technology enterprise.  To meet that vision, Lockheed Martin will continue to build on its history of success in identifying and capitalizing on key information systems, electronic, aerospace, and energy technologies.  The Corporation is organized into four core business areas: Aeronautical Systems, Space Systems, Electronic Systems, and Information Systems & Global Services.   Within these four businesses are nearly fifty major businesses with locations in most of the fifty states and around the world.','n','n','n','y','y','y','y','y','y','','n','','','',0,0,0,'','y',3,'','',0,'n'),(40,'2008-06-19 17:35:01','EMC Corporation','','176 South Street','','Hopkinton','MA','01748','US','','','','n','n','n','','','','','','','','','','','',0,0,0,'','n',0,'','',0,'n'),(42,'2008-06-19 18:34:29','Westinghouse Electric Company','','4350 Northern Pike','','Monroeville, PA','','15146','US','','Large (>500 employees)','Westinghouse provides a wide range of nuclear plant products and customer services throughout the world, including fuel, spent-fuel management, service and maintenance, instrumentation and control, and training. We’re the largest supplier of both nuclear fuels and services in the United States, and the second largest in the world.\r\nThrough our three core businesses—Nuclear Fuel, Nuclear Services, and Nuclear Power Plants—we’re committed to delivering superior services and value to our utility customers worldwide. By strategically aligning our goals with theirs and by forming partnerships, we anticipate and quickly respond